<TITLE> 9 bodies found after Kishoreganj, Madaripur trawler accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Madaripur, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com)  Two more bodies were recovered on Saturday after two trawlers capsized in Kishoreganj and Madaripur earlier in the week, taking the combined body toll of the two accidents to nine. One body was recovered at Mithamoin Upazila in Kishoreganj after a trawler sank there with two crew and eight passengers on board during rough weather on Thursday afternoon. Two crewmen and four passengers managed to swim to shore at the time. Upazila Nirbahi Officer Gopal Chandra Saha told bdnews24.com that the body of former member of Mithamoin Union Parishad, Pratap Chandra Das, was recovered at around 9am Saturday. The bodies of Mithamoin deputy assistant agriculture officer Nurul Islam, 35, and local doctor Rahid Fakir, 65, were recovered on Friday. One passenger was still missing, presumed dead, Saha said. Another body was recovered from the Arialkhan river on Saturday, taking the total body count to five after a trawler carrying a bridal party, with a total of 53 passengers and crew aboard, was hit by a sand laden vessel on Wednesday night. The trawler went down near Char Manair at Shibchar Upazila in Madaripur. Thirty-three people managed to swim to safety. Another twelve were rescued from the water. Shibchar police chief MA Jalil told bdnews24.com four bodies were recovered on Friday afternoon. He said divers had subsequently recovered the body of 70-year old Barek Farazi at around 8am Saturday. The rescue operation was still underway as three passengers were still missing, said Jalil. bdn
